    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_gt.00033_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Mickle St: Camden<ptr target="loc.04796_n4"/></name>
                    <date when="1891-09-06">Sept: 6 '91</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friends all&#8212;</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Seems quite a while since I have seen any of you, or heard f'm you, 
                George or Harry,<ptr target="n0590"/> or any&#8212;Hope 
                &#38; pray it is going all smoothly with you all&#8212;I 
                am still slowly getting along much on the same way as of late years, 
                ("always sick but never die")&#8212;got out yesterday to the Cemetery<ptr target="loc.07329_n5b"/> 
                for a short drive&#8212;&#38; have eaten 
                quite a hearty breakfast this forenoon&#8212;So you see I keep up sort 
                o'&#8212;Dr Bucke<ptr target="n0119"/> has return'd f'm England<ptr target="loc.02447_n6"/> 
                &#38; is here at present&#8212;well &#38; hearty&#8212;He 
                saw Edward Carpenter<ptr target="n0141b"/> who is well &#38; flourishing&#8212;Mrs 
                O'Connor<ptr target="n4137"/> has been here a week 
                returns to Wash'n to morrow&#8212;Did you get the August 
                <hi rend="underline">Lippincott's</hi><ptr target="loc.08153_n3"/> magazine? 
                I am more helpless than ever, or I sh'd come down 
                &#38; see you&#8212;sister<ptr target="loc.04792_n3"/> &#38; bro:<ptr target="n0700"/> at Burlington N J are well&#8212; 
                own sister<ptr target="n0285"/> Burlington Vermont sick &#38; poorly&#8212;my bro: 
                Ed<ptr target="n1047"/> all right&#8212;remembrance &#38; love to all, to you &#38; George &#38; Harry &#38; Eva<ptr target="loc.04006_n3"/> &#38; 
                Ed<ptr target="n0589e"/> &#38; Debby<ptr target="n0844c"/> &#38; all&#8212;  
            </p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_gt.00034_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
